caption.title: Predicted Iiwi density (per km 2) for sterile/incompatible male mosquitoes under RCP8.5, A1B, and RCP4.5 climate projections at mid elevation.
caption.p: Model baseline (red line) means no release of modified (sterile or incompatible) mosquitoes, other lines show continuous release of 500 modified male mosquitoes per km 2 for 9 months with mate competition coefficient (C = 0.5) between modified and wild male mosquito and different magnitudes of egg mortality (EM, blue line for EM = 0.90, and green line for EM = 0.95).
